2.What are the advantages of taking a taxi compared with buses.
Compared with buses, a taxi obviously had many advantages. Firstly, you don't need to worry that there's no seat, since you can always get a seat on the taxi. Also, taking a taxi is faster than taking abus, because it can arrive the destination directly.

3.Is it convenient to take the bus/taxi in your city?
Yes, it's really convenient. There's a bus stop alomst every block. For me, I take a bus to work everyday. It's both cheap and convenient.

Public Transportation
1.What's the most popular means of transportation in your hometown?
Bus is the most popular means of transportation in my hometown. But the nearest bus station is half mile away and there's only one bus passing every twenty minutes. You'll get frustrated if you miss a bus.

2.How often do you take a buses.
I take a bus to work everyday. I am a moron in driving, but taking a bus is both cheap and convenient and you don't have to drive yourself. However, when stuck in traffic jams, you may feel anxious.

3.Can you compare the advantages of plane and trains?
Well, for me, I would say, with train, you can get up and move around during the journey, and you can also enjoy the beautiful senery along the trip. While an advantage of taking the plane is that it can save time and it allows you to reach any place in the world.

4.Is driving to work popular in your country?
I don't think so. In China, traffic jams often happen in rush hour, especially in rainy days. So most people choose to go to work by subway since it has the merit of convenient, shortcut and vast capacity.

5.Do you think people will drive more in the future?
No, because the government in China encourage people to drive less, so more and more people choose to take public tranportations. You konw, the traffic situation is overly bad during rush hours, and taking public transportations like subway is both cheap and convenient.

6.Would you ride bikes to work in the future?
No, because my company is pretty close to me, it's just a ten minutes walk. So I don't really need a bike to get there.

7.What will become the most popular means of 
transportation in China?
I think that will be the subway. Well, I think subways will become the most popular means of transport for urban development because of its efficiency, punctuaily, low pollution. 

8.Do you prefer public transportation or private transportation?
I prefer public transportation. I used public tranportation all the time to get to home. The tranportation in big city is crap. So owning your own cai or taking a taxi isn't such a good idea. You could be stuck in traffic forever plus expenses for gas and parking garage.

