Yes of course. Just like I said, I learned to play the violin when I was only 4 years old so I had to listen to a lot of music played by violin when I was a child.

16.What kinds of music are (most)popular in China? 
It depends. For young people, I think most of them prefer pop music. And in recent years, maybe music from Europe, Japan and Korea is particularly popular. For mid-aged and old people, they may be fond of traditional music such as Beijing opera.

Color
1.What colour do you like best? / What's your favourite color ?Why?   
I prefer red. In China, red is associated with life and good luck. A traditional Chinese bride wears something red on her wedding day, such as her wedding gown and handkerchief used to cover her head, in the hope that it will bring her and her bridegroom some luck in future.

2.What’s the most popular color in China?
Colours mean many different things to different people and cultures.I think red is the most popular colour in China. For example, many Chinese people including me tend to think of red as a lucky color. On Chinese new year eve, parents like to dress their children in red, which contains the best wishing from adults.

3.Do you like to wear clothes or bright colors?
Yes, as I am an easy going type of person, I really like bright colours. So I usually wear clothes in orange, yellow,or red.

4.What’s the difference between men and women’s preference on colors?
Sure, well, I think men and women have different preference on colours, what I mean is, women are more romantic ,so they choose something like warm colours, while men usually are more stable, so they prefer dark colours.

5.Do colors affect your mood?
Sure. Colors can affect the way we feel. It can affect our moods in either a positive or negative manner.Light colors usually make me feel delight, while dark colors make me feel depressed.

Being in a hurry
1.When was the last time you did something in a hurry?
Last Monday, I slept in late by accident and got dressed in a hurry. I just picked something up off of the floor and slung it on. I didn't realize I had put on a shirt that was filthy dirty until I arrived at work and one of my colleagues pointed it out to me. It was so embarrassing.

2.Do you like to finish things quickly?
Yes, I do. I'm always being in a rush.If that's the case then I think I definitely suffer from hurry-sickness. I feel like I'm wasting time if I take too long to get from A to B or to finish a task. I like to feel like I'm being efficient and this probably leads me to hurry.

3.What kinds of things will you never do in a hurry?
If I’m going on holiday I always try to pack my bags diligently, usually by setting some time aside and doing it well in advance. There's nothing worse than arriving to your destination without something you really need, or even worse, getting to the airport and realising you don’t have your passport!

4.Why do people make mistakes more easily when they are in a hurry?
As the saying goes, "more speed, less haste". Things rarely work out the way you want them to when you rush, because people will always be less careful and forgetful when they are in a hurry. So in the long run, doing something well once is quicker than doing it twice.

Bicycle
1.Do you like riding a bicycle?[why?/why not?]
Well, I like to ride bikes for a few reasons. The main reason I like riding bikes is that I think it is a really fun and it is a good way to go sightseeing. I’d also like to point-out that riding a bike is very good for
my health because it can help me to lose weight. I would also like to add that recently I have not been able to ride my bike much, as I am quite busy at work.

2.Is it difficult to learn how to ride a bicycle?
not a bit, I think most kids can get the hang of it in one day. the initial stage of learning is all about balancing and it may be a little tricky for learners. But soon you will know it that, once our bike catches the speed, it will get balanced automatically. everything become natural.

3.Is it popular to ride bicycles in your country?
Definitely yes. Maybe it is not all the rage, but for the formal bicycle kingdom, a huge chunk of the population still use bicycles on a daily basis. it is a good and necessary way to go around.

4.When was the last time you used your bicycle?
well, that’s a good question and really bring some bad memory back. It’s nearly two years since the last time I rode a bicycle and it is when she got stolen. That was a rainy night and I insisted on riding home from work despite a frizzle. But soon it turned too heavy for cycling and I have to deal with the bicycle. So I locked it up to the pavement rails where it could be sheltered. The next day I got there, it was gone. the end of the story.

5.Do you think bicycle is very convenient for people to use in modern life?
Yes, it was, it is , and it will be convenient tool for people to use for going around. cos it is easy to learn and afford, and it is so often faster than cars in urban commuting when traffic jams are a daily routine. Let alone cycling is one of the best and funniest way to keep fit.

Computer
1.Do you use computers very much?
Yes, I almost use my computer every day since I basically need it for study, online-chatting, and for reading.

2.Have computers changed your life anyway?
I think computers have greatly changed my life since it allows me to take online-courses and online-shopping also brings us much convenience.

3.Do you think computers are useful in everyday life?
Sure. Computers bring us a lot of benefits. In contemporary society, people depend largely on computers to work and study. Computers are so useful that people almost can’t live without them. 
4.Do you think there are any disadvantages to use computers?
Yes. Some children may get harmful information online, and many people have become addicted to computer games. The computer radiation also has a detrimental effect on people’s health.
Computers are now used a lot in education. 
5.What do you think of this?
Undoubtedly, computers can become wonderful study tools for children if used properly. By using computers, children may learn faster, become more creative and absorb a variety of knowledge.

Hancraft
1.Do you like to collect things made by hand?
No, I am not a collector of any kind. The only thing that can fall into the category is a paper rose that I learnt to make in the hope of making some difference about that relationship, but to no avail.

2.Did you ever take handcrafts lessons at school?
Yes, there were labour skill lessons when I was in the preliminary school. But guess what, it was one of many courses called subsidiary course that would always be marginalized. so skill acquired.

3.Did you ever made anything by hand when you were a child?
of course, every kid once wished to be a good stuff maker that can create the special out of the ordinary. clumsy as I am, the best thing I can make is the paper plane. it is cheap, easy to make, and most importantly it was great fun to set it free out of windows and see it sliding in the wind.

4.Do you think handcrafts are meaningful activities?
Of course it is fundamentally meaningful. there is a time when craftsmen were highly respected and blue-collar jobs are widely desired in china. It is a pity that this era is gone. I always admire those who can make some wooden, paper, steel gadgets from some basic materials, and who can fix the house wire/drainage/toilet problem by their own, I believe every kids want that kind of father and every girl wants that kind of husband. That skill makes you resourceful, dependable and thus trustworthy.

5.Do you think children should learn more about handcraft?
Definitely yes especially it is an age when the whole fancy electronic devices mesmerise children like drugs. Children are more than ever in need of being pulled away from the screen and having some real and constructive contact with the real material world. Learning through making by hand is best way I can imagine for children to fully explore their creative potential. And as say, it is pure fun.

6.Is there anything that you would like to make by hand in the future?
I currently keep three deserted baby cats and they are temporarily living in a cardboard, so I would like to build three independent cat houses by hand and tools, and maybe a loo as well. The whole thing is still in the making and I hope they can be newly housed soon.

Science
1.Do you like science?
Yes, I like science very much. When I was young, my dream was to become a scientist, and now I deeply believe that science is very important to our lives. There is no doubt that science has made our lives much more convenient.

2.Are there many science museums in your hometown?
I guess yes, like the Beijing Science and Technology Museum.

3.Did you like science classes when you were young?

4.Do you think schoolchildren should have both art classes and science classes?
Well, that depends. It’s hard to say cos for students who have an extremely keen interest in a certain subject that they also excel at, I don’t think it’s necessary to learn both; but for those who don’t show a particular preference, maybe it’s better to integrate art classes with science classes.

5.Do you think science is important to your society?
Yes, I think science plays an important role in our socitey. It has largely promote our working efficiency and productivity. Physics helps us figure out how things work. Chemistry shows us the structure of the world and how materials interact with each other. Biology teaches us where living things come from and what living things need to survive.

Study efficency
1.Do you prefer to study in the morning or in the evening?
I prefer to study in the morning cos my mind is active after a good rest at night. We have the old saying: the best season during a day is the morning.

2.Why do some people find it difficult to focus in the morning?
I reckon because they don’t have a good rest, say they stayed up late the night before. Some people have really irregular timetables.

3.What do you do to improve your learning efficiency?
I would say, to integrate work with leisure, have a clear division of work and rest by making a clear schedule. Keeping a good mood also matters a lot.

